  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6769.78 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6770 (-13.8B) and positive gamma at 6780 (+10.2B), dealers are caught in a high-volatility pocket where they'll aggressively buy any dip toward 6765-6770 and sell any pop toward 6780-6800. The 384% 1-minute GEX surge indicates massive options flow just hit, likely creating this tight gamma sandwich that should pin price action in the near term. Key levels are crystal clear: 6770 downside support where dealers become forced buyers, and 6780-6800 resistance where they turn into sellers.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy action stuck between 6770-6780 with dealers acting as shock absorbers on both sides.",
